1.What is Continuous Integration (CI)
Definition:
Continuous Integration is a process where developers 
frequently integrate code, and Jenkins automatically:
• Builds the project 
• Runs tests 
• Reports results
2. Open Jenkins Dashboard
http://localhost:8080
3. Create New CI Project
• Click New Item
Enter an item name: 
• Select:
Freestyle Project
• Click OK
4. Configure Source Code (Git Integration)
Scroll to:
Source Code Management
Select Git
Enter repository URL:
• Specify the Git branch name
5. Add Build Tool (Maven Integration)
Scroll to:
Build Section
Click:
Add Build Step → Invoke top-level Maven targets
Goals: Clean install
This command: Cleans old build,Compilescode,Runstests                      
Creates build file
Click on: Advanced
Enter pom.xml to read the pom file
(Optional) Gradle Integration
Instead of Maven:
Choose:
Invoke Gradle Script
Save the Project
Click:
Save
6. Run CI Pipeline (Build Now)
Click:
Build Now
7. View Console Output (Most Important)
Click:
Build #1 
Console Output
