🎯 Aim
To deploy applications using Azure DevOps Release Pipelines, manage secrets using Azure Key Vault, and perform Continuous Deployment using Azure Pipelines.
 
🛠️ Requirements
• Azure DevOps account 
• Microsoft Azure account 
• Maven/Gradle project 
• GitHub repository or Azure Repos 
• Azure App Service created 
 
What is Release Pipeline?
A Release Pipeline automates deployment of applications after successful build completion.
It helps in:
• Continuous Deployment 
• Automated releases 
• Faster delivery 
• Reduced manual work 
 
🔄 Workflow
Developer → GitHub → Azure Pipeline → Build → Release Pipeline → Azure App Service
 
📌 Step-by-Step Procedure
 
🔹 Step 1: Login to Azure DevOps
Open browser and visit:
Azure DevOps Official Website
Login using Microsoft account.
 
🔹 Step 2: Open Existing Project
Select your Azure DevOps project.
 
🔹 Step 3: Create Azure App Service
Open Azure Portal:
Microsoft Azure Portal
Go to:
Create Resource → Web App
Enter:
• App Name 
• Runtime Stack 
• Region 
Click:
Create
 
🔹 Step 4: Create Azure Pipeline
Go to:
Pipelines → Create Pipeline
Select:
• GitHub
OR 
• Azure Repos 
 
🔹 Step 5: Configure Build Pipeline
Add YAML configuration:
trigger:
- main

pool:
  vmImage: ubuntu-latest

steps:
- task: Maven@3
  inputs:
    mavenPomFile: 'pom.xml'
    goals: 'clean package'
 
🔹 Step 6: Run Build Pipeline
Click:
Save and Run
Observe:
• Build success 
• Artifact generation 
 
🔹 Step 7: Publish Build Artifact
Add artifact publish task:
- task: PublishBuildArtifacts@1
  inputs:
    pathToPublish: 'target'
    artifactName: 'drop'
Run pipeline again.
 
🔹 Step 8: Create Release Pipeline
Go to:
Pipelines → Releases
Click:
New Release Pipeline
 
🔹 Step 9: Select Deployment Template
Choose:
Azure App Service Deployment
Click:
Apply
 
🔹 Step 10: Add Artifact
Click:
Add Artifact
Select:
• Source Type → Build 
• Build Pipeline 
Click:
Add
 
🔹 Step 11: Configure Deployment Stage
Click Stage:
Stage 1
Configure:
• Azure Subscription 
• App Service Name 
 
🔹 Step 12: Enable Continuous Deployment
Click:
Continuous Deployment Trigger
Enable:
ON
Now deployment starts automatically after every successful build.
 
🔹 Step 13: Create Azure Key Vault
Open Azure Portal.
Go to:
Create Resource → Key Vault
Enter:
• Vault Name 
• Resource Group 
• Region 
Click:
Create
 
🔹 Step 14: Add Secret to Key Vault
Open Key Vault.
Go to:
Secrets → Generate/Import
Add:
• Secret Name 
• Secret Value 
Example:
DB_PASSWORD
 
🔹 Step 15: Link Key Vault with Pipeline
In Release Pipeline:
Go to:
Variables → Variable Groups
Select:
Link secrets from Azure Key Vault
Choose:
• Azure Subscription 
• Key Vault 
Save configuration.
🔹 Step 16: Deploy Application
Create release manually or trigger automatically.
Pipeline performs:
✔ Build
✔ Test
✔ Deploy
🔹 Step 17: Verify Deployment
Open browser:
https://<app-name>.azurewebsites.net
Verify application is running successfully."//